opening_comment: How could the Great Barrier Reef be represented in OSM?  The GBR is protected by the Great Barrier Reef Marine Park, and also as a  World Heritage Site. I haven't found these in OSM data.  There is a map with coordinates for the Park and the WHS area: http://www.gbrmpa.gov.au/__data/assets/pdf_file/0020/4457/GBR-general-reference-A3-March-2012.PDF  I found a way and a relation, both to the east of the protected reef area: http://www.openstreetmap.org/browse/way/162217874 http://www.openstreetmap.org/browse/relation/968374 The way is tagged with natural=reef, the relation is a multipolygon with some boundary=maritime tags on its members.  Could we create a new area with the data from the government map?
